How to choose mattress and box spring: women and men look for different things
No pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality on a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the box spring.
First and foremosm they must be perfectly complemented to suit specific users.
During the election, numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and box spring are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they are "heated" more slowly.
In addition, they tend to weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the center channels are not properly aerated and above are on a firm base, they keep moisture inside. Mold may even appear underneath.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
"Almost every hockey player who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here."
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"These types of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes that weather nervous system problems, so they receive poor joint and skin information," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other clients, have long preferred memory foam mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes your stiffness and shape based on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing puts pressure on it; during the night, it won't spin like after a hard game.
He just falls asleep better.
Viscoelastic also works as protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add the length of your feet to its height, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
For single rooms, e.g. single rooms, at least 120 to 140 cm are recommended.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably shrunk towards your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, an expert from Cechu'alouník to dekoratér, who has been dealing with the problem of healthy sleep and furniture ergonomics for many years, a topic she teaches in specialized schools.
In the double rooms, each needs its own box spring and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the sleeping boxes at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interiors a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeter are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you settle on the mattress, you certainly shouldn't notice the springs," says Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of box spring.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe poorly and you can't wash your cover, which is often done today.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
Therefore, the sellers give a tip: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care carefully of cleaning and washing the cover, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although zippered mattress covers are currently manufactured around its perimeter, so when opened they stay in two parts (something very important for washing and washing machine size!), their handling on larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress may seem like a fight between a flyweight and a heavyweight.
In bed, instead of a box spring, do you have a firm board?
Never!
At most for the beds designed for overnight visitors.
However, you should make (if you don't already have them) ventilation holes in the board and it should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulable sheet boxes containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) can be used, although a box spring with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the lumbar sheets are reinforced and their rigidity can always be regulated.
Articulable sheet springs should not be used with a spring mattress as it does not react to recline.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the blades, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "surround" the shoulders perfectly during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "male", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember the women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are springs with cross structure or tablets with the so-called multi-torque damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is lowered.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the right mattress and box spring, if you use a bad pillow (large and "fluffy"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of the same can be relaxed.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, which is normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on its side, the pillow should be on the same level (when combined with the shoulder-reinforced box spring or the softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses have something to do with the original mattresses stuffed with straw.
Manufacturers continue to use, increasingly, natural materials or at least mixtures.
In fact, organic mattresses are fashionable.
Petroleum-based raw materials, with which polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, such as castor or soybeans.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vasí-ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma of forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with vegetable extracts of breeze, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and refreshes the body, women prefer to "heat" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel more warmth.
Currently favorites?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with a structure of adapted cells, which makes them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various rigidity of cold and viscoelastic foam allows to manufacture mattresses from various areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand kronor up.
Those who play a therapeutic function tend to have lower VAT, as they are considered as health means.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It's hard to save on mattresses and sleeping boxes.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a Memory memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 kronor.
The second is obtained for free.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cell structure and high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during takeoffs astronauts were subjected to enormous overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used on mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and soothe them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents are using people tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track people's movement and thus contribute, for example, in case such as the disappearance of nine-year-old Ani-ka Janatková.
At the moment the device is about the size of a matchbox, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the case of the defunct Anyka and began to learn about the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We're all trying to tell ourselves that it's not about spying, it's another means of reducing the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they get into someone's purse without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bosková warns of the fact that if the child doesn't want to wear it, she'll just throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled."
"Before, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but they could be turned off as easily as the tracking device," says Bosková.
In its view, it is debatable whether in the event of an attack such a device is really useful.
"If it is a prepared abduction, the author will practically always check if the child is carrying any kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices spreads, it will also look for them, since their sale will certainly be done with a lot of advertising."
"In such cases, criminals are always one step ahead of the police," she says.
However, it adds that such devices can help in the event of an impromptu attack by a pedophile.
According to THE RC Monitoring company's Robert Eech, which provides tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"You can set the device to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If it is damaged, it will at least facilitate the last position of the person concerned."
"The most expensive devices have a tilt meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and sits still, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Eech.
In his view, such a service can be obtained even with mobile phones with navigation, where only special software should be installed.
The problem with today's tracking units is that at the moment these are devices that are similar in size to a matchbox or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they may be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, for this reason tests are currently being carried out on devices that look like a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential aggressor may not identify the device."
"Or identify him after a certain amount of time, which can make the police gain time," he adds.
